label.value: constitutional megaloblastic anemia with severe neurologic disease

value.value: Any osteogenesis imperfecta in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the SERPINH1 gene.
An inherited condition caused by mutation(s) in the ITPA gene, encoding inosine triphosphate pyrophosphatase. It is characterized by elevated concentrations of inosine triphosphate in erythrocytes.
Any dextro-looped transposition of the great arteries in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the GDF1 gene.
Episodic ataxia type 5 (EA5) is an extremely rare form of Hereditary episodic ataxia characterized by recurrent episodes of vertigo and ataxia lasting several hours.

label.value: generalized epilepsy with febrile seizures plus, type 7

value.value: Any generalized epilepsy with febrile seizures plus in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the SCN9A gene.
Any hypertrophic cardiomyopathy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the JPH2 gene.
Any hypertrophic cardiomyopathy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the CALR3 gene.
Any hypertrophic cardiomyopathy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the NEXN gene.
Any familial isolated dilated cardiomyopathy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the BAG3 gene.

Monosomy 13q14 is a rare chromosomal anomaly syndrome, resulting from a partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 13, characterized by developmental delay, variable degrees of intellectual disability, retinoblastoma and craniofacial dysmorphism (incl. micro/dolichocephaly, high and broad forehead, prominent eyebrows, thick, anteverted ear lobes, short nose with a broad nasal bridge and bulbous tip, prominent philtrum, large mouth with thin upper lip and thick, everted lower lip). Other features reported include high birth weight, macrocephaly, pinealoma, hepatomegaly, inguinal hernia and cryptorchidism.

Spinocerebellar ataxia type 35 (SCA35) is a subtype of autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia type 1 (ADCA type 1) characterized by the adult-onset of progressive gait and limb ataxia, dysarthria, ocular dysmetria, intention tremor, hyperreflexia and spasmodic torticollis.
Spinocerebellar ataxia type 32 (SCA32) is a subtype of autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia type 1 (ADCA type 1) characterized by ataxia, cognitive impairment and azoospermia in males.

label.value: recurrent Neisseria infections due to factor D deficiency

value.value: Any autosomal recessive nonsyndromic deafness in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the KARS gene.
Any Fanconi anemia in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the SLX4 gene.

label.value: frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 6

value.value: Any amyotrophic lateral sclerosis in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the VCP gene.
Any azoospermia in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the NR5A1 gene.
Alpha thalassemia caused by variation in three of the four copies of the alpha hemoglobin genes (e.g., large deletion in HBA1 and HBA2 genes in trans with a variant in either HBA1 or HBA2).
Any familial atrial fibrillation in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the KCNJ2 gene.
Any hypotrichosis in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the KRT74 gene.
Abnormal clinical manifestations of beta thalassemia that are as a result of the underlying genotype.
Any combined pituitary hormone deficiencies, genetic form in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the OTX2 gene.
A dyskeratosis congenita that has material basis in an autosomal dominant mutation of TERT on chromosome 5p15.33.
A dyskeratosis congenita that has material basis in an autosomal dominant mutation of TINF2 on chromosome 14q12.

label.value: obsolete bleeding diathesis due to thromboxane synthesis deficiency

value.value: Any progressive myoclonic epilepsy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the GOSR2 gene.
Any lissencephaly in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the NDE1 gene.
Any familial atrial fibrillation in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the SCN5A gene.

3-Phosphoserine phosphatase deficiency is an extremely rare form of serine deficiency syndrome characterized clinically by congenital microcephaly and severe psychomotor retardation in the single reported case to date, which was associated with Williams syndrome.

label.value: hyperlipidemia due to hepatic triglyceride lipase deficiency

value.value: Hyperlipidemia due to hepatic triacylglycerol lipase deficiency is a rare, genetic hyperalphalipoproteinemia characterized by elevated plasma cholesterol and triglyceride (TG) levels with a marked TG enrichment of low- and high-density lipoproteins (HDL), presence of circulating beta-very low density lipoproteins and elevated HDL cholesterol levels, in the presence of a very low, or undetectable, postheparin plasma hepatic lipase activity. Premature atherosclerosis and/or coronary heart disease may be associated.

Leukotriene C4 synthase deficiency is an extremely rare fatal neurometabolic developmental disorder characterized clinically by muscular hypotonia, psychomotor retardation, failure to thrive, and microcephaly.
Deafness - lymphedema - leukemia is a very rare, serious syndromic genetic disorder characterized by primary lymphedema, immunodeficiency, and hematological disorders.

label.value: complex cortical dysplasia with other brain malformations 1

value.value: Any complex cortical dysplasia with other brain malformations in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the TUBB3 gene.
Any Moyamoya disease in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ACTA2 gene.
Any familial atrial fibrillation in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ABCC9 gene.
